HEADWORD: Trachearia
<hw>Tra`che*a"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of Arachnida
including those that breathe only by means of tracheae. It includes the
mites, ticks, false scorpions, and harvestmen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

